.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2024" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIoption\fR] ...

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple command-line interpreter that provides a user interface to access the services of the operating system. It executes commands read from the standard input.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-n\fR
Run the shell in non-interactive mode.
.TP
\fB-h\fR
Display help information about the shell usage.

.SH USAGE
.B simple_shell
starts the shell, providing a prompt to the user where they can enter commands.

.PP
The shell reads commands from the standard input, parses them, and then executes them. The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.BI exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.BI env
Display the current environment variables.

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
.B simple_shell
executes commands by creating a child process using
.BR fork (2),
which executes the command using
.BR execve (2).
The parent process waits for the child process to terminate with
.BR waitpid (2).

.SH EXAMPLES
Run the shell in interactive mode:
.RS
.B $ ./simple_shell
.RE

Run a command using non-interactive mode:
.RS
.B $ echo "ls -l" | ./simple_shell
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B simple_shell
utilizes the
.B PATH
environment variable to locate executable files.

.SH AUTHORS
Simple Shell was written by [Your Name] and [Partner's Name].

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR waitpid (2)

